{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_28ada805effeKVkAJHcvBKMXXi","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d7525985d0015hw61MnzDSRc2B","parts":[{"id":"prt_d7525a08f001s5o1NTlYlDwYxj","messageID":"msg_d7525985d0015hw61MnzDSRc2B","sessionID":"ses_28ada805effeKVkAJHcvBKMXXi","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_17c81f8fd41b4f90adec5c25","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md"},"output":"<path>/workspace/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: <a href=\"https://sentry.io/?utm_source=github&utm_medium=logo\" target=\"_blank\">\n2:   <img src=\"https://sentry-brand.storage.googleapis.com/github-banners/github-sdk-python.png\" alt=\"Sentry for Python\">\n3: </a>\n4: <div align=\"center\">\n5: \n6: _Bad software is everywhere, and we're tired of it. Sentry is on a mission to help developers write better software faster, so we can get back to enjoying technology. If you want to join us\n7: [<kbd>**Check out our open positions**</kbd>](https://sentry.io/careers/)_.\n8: \n9: [![Discord](https://img.shields.io/discord/621778831602221064?logo=discord&labelColor=%20%235462eb&logoColor=%20%23f5f5f5&color=%20%235462eb)](https://discord.com/invite/Ww9hbqr)\n10: [![X Follow](https://img.shields.io/twitter/follow/sentry?label=sentry&style=social)](https://x.com/intent/follow?screen_name=sentry)\n11: [![PyPi page link -- version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/sentry-sdk.svg)](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/sentry-sdk)\n12: <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.7 | 3.8 | 3.9 | 3.10 | 3.11 | 3.12 | 3.13 | 3.14-blue.svg\" alt=\"python\">\n13: [![Build Status](https://github.com/getsentry/sentry-python/actions/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/getsentry/sentry-python/actions/workflows/ci.yml)\n14: \n15: <br/>\n16: \n17: </div>\n18: \n19: \n20: # Official Sentry SDK for Python\n21: \n22: Welcome to the official Python SDK for **[Sentry](http://sentry.io/)**.\n23: \n24: \n25: ## 📦 Getting Started\n26: \n27: ### Prerequisites\n28: \n29: You need a Sentry [account](https://sentry.io/signup/) and [project](https://docs.sentry.io/product/projects/).\n30: \n31: ### Installation\n32: \n33: Getting Sentry into your project is straightforward. Just run this command in your terminal:\n34: \n35: ```bash\n36: pip install --upgrade sentry-sdk\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ### Basic Configuration\n40: \n41: Here's a quick configuration example to get Sentry up and running:\n42: \n43: ```python\n44: import sentry_sdk\n45: \n46: sentry_sdk.init(\n47:     \"https://12927b5f211046b575ee51fd8b1ac34f@o1.ingest.sentry.io/1\",  # Your DSN here\n48: \n49:     # Set traces_sample_rate to 1.0 to capture 100%\n50:     # of traces for performance monitoring.\n51:     traces_sample_rate=1.0,\n52: )\n53: ```\n54: \n55: With this configuration, Sentry will monitor for exceptions and performance issues.\n56: \n57: ### Quick Usage Example\n58: \n59: To generate some events that will show up in Sentry, you can log messages or capture errors:\n60: \n61: ```python\n62: import sentry_sdk\n63: sentry_sdk.init(...)  # same as above\n64: \n65: sentry_sdk.capture_message(\"Hello Sentry!\")  # You'll see this in your Sentry dashboard.\n66: \n67: raise ValueError(\"Oops, something went wrong!\")  # This will create an error event in Sentry.\n68: ```\n69: \n70: \n71: ## 📚 Documentation\n72: \n73: For more details on advanced usage, integrations, and customization, check out the full documentation on [https://docs.sentry.io](https://docs.sentry.io/).\n74: \n75: \n76: ## 🧩 Integrations\n77: \n78: Sentry integrates with a ton of popular Python libraries and frameworks, including [FastAPI](https://docs.sentry.io/platforms/python/integrations/fastapi/), [Django](https://docs.sentry.io/platforms/python/integrations/django/), [Celery](https://docs.sentry.io/platforms/python/integrations/celery/), [OpenAI](https://docs.sentry.io/platforms/python/integrations/openai/) and many, many more.  Check out the [full list of integrations](https://docs.sentry.io/platforms/python/integrations/) to get the full picture.\n79: \n80: \n81: ## 🚧 Migrating Between Versions?\n82: \n83: ### From `1.x` to `2.x`\n84: \n85: If you're using the older `1.x` version of the SDK, now's the time to upgrade to `2.x`. It includes significant upgrades and new features. Check our [migration guide](https://docs.sentry.io/platforms/python/migration/1.x-to-2.x) for assistance.\n86: \n87: ### From `raven-python`\n88: \n89: Using the legacy `raven-python` client? It's now in maintenance mode, and we recommend migrating to the new SDK for an improved experience. Get all the details in our [migration guide](https://docs.sentry.io/platforms/python/migration/raven-to-sentry-sdk/).\n90: \n91: \n92: ## 🙌 Want to Contribute?\n93: \n94: We'd love your help in improving the Sentry SDK! Whether it's fixing bugs, adding features, writing new integrations, or enhancing documentation, every contribution is valuable.\n95: \n96: For details on how to contribute, please read our [contribution guide](CONTRIBUTING.md) and explore the [open issues](https://github.com/getsentry/sentry-python/issues).\n97: \n98: \n99: ## 🛟 Need Help?\n100: \n101: If you encounter issues or need help setting up or configuring the SDK, don't hesitate to reach out to the [Sentry Community on Discord](https://discord.com/invite/Ww9hbqr). There is a ton of great people there ready to help!\n102: \n103: \n104: ## 🔗 Resources\n105: \n106: Here are all resources to help you make the most of Sentry:\n107: \n108: - [Documentation](https://docs.sentry.io/platforms/python/) - Official documentation to get started.\n109: - [Discord](https://discord.com/invite/Ww9hbqr) - Join our Discord community.\n110: - [X/Twitter](https://x.com/intent/follow?screen_name=sentry) -  Follow us on X (Twitter) for updates.\n111: - [Stack Overflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/sentry) - Questions and answers related to Sentry.\n112: \n113: <a name=\"license\"></a>\n114: ## 📃 License\n115: \n116: The SDK is open-source and available under the MIT license. Check out the [LICENSE](LICENSE) file for more information.\n117: \n118: \n119: ## 😘 Contributors\n120: \n121: Thanks to everyone who has helped improve the SDK!\n122: \n123: <a href=\"https://github.com/getsentry/sentry-python/graphs/contributors\">\n124:   <img src=\"https://contributors-img.web.app/image?repo=getsentry/sentry-python\" />\n125: </a>\n\n(End of file - total 125 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"<a href=\"https://sentry.io/?utm_source=github&utm_medium=logo\" target=\"_blank\">\n  <img src=\"https://sentry-brand.storage.googleapis.com/github-banners/github-sdk-python.png\" alt=\"Sentry for Python\">\n</a>\n<div align=\"center\">\n\n_Bad software is everywhere, and we're tired of it. Sentry is on a mission to help developers write better software faster, so we can get back to enjoying technology. If you want to join us\n[<kbd>**Check out our open positions**</kbd>](https://sentry.io/careers/)_.\n\n[![Discord](https://img.shields.io/discord/621778831602221064?logo=discord&labelColor=%20%235462eb&logoColor=%20%23f5f5f5&color=%20%235462eb)](https://discord.com/invite/Ww9hbqr)\n[![X Follow](https://img.shields.io/twitter/follow/sentry?label=sentry&style=social)](https://x.com/intent/follow?screen_name=sentry)\n[![PyPi page link -- version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/sentry-sdk.svg)](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/sentry-sdk)\n<img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.7 | 3.8 | 3.9 | 3.10 | 3.11 | 3.12 | 3.13 | 3.14-blue.svg\" alt=\"python\">\n[![Build Status](https://github.com/getsentry/sentry-python/actions/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/getsentry/sentry-python/actions/workflows/ci.yml)\n\n<br/>\n\n</div>\n\n\n# Official Sentry SDK for Python","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"README.md","time":{"start":1775786893741,"end":1775786893744}}}]}
